<p><img src="https://cdn3.brettterpstra.com/uploads/2025/10/iterm-pugin-header-rb.7508.jpg" width="800" height="226" style="margin:0 auto;clear:both;" class="header" /></p>
<p>I&rsquo;ve published a tiny Jekyll plugin that makes terminal commands in posts runnable with a click (in iTerm, at least).</p>

<p>The <a href="https://github.com/ttscoff/JekyllPlugins/tree/master/iTerm">iTerm tag plugin</a> renders a fenced code block showing a command, and a &ldquo;Run in iTerm&rdquo; link that uses iTerm 2&rsquo;s new(ish) command url scheme (<code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">iterm2:/command?c=COMMAND</code>) to open the command in a confirmation box in iTerm, ready for immediate execution.</p>

<p>The plugin outputs fenced code blocks with language definitions, so whatever syntax highlighter your Jekyll blog uses can still appropriately highlight the code. The &ldquo;Run in iTerm&rdquo; link is given a little extra markup to make it easy to style.</p>

<h3 id="examples">Examples</h3>

<p>If you&rsquo;re running iTerm, click the link below the code blocks to open
the command in a confirmation dialog.</p>

<p>Short form:</p>

<div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight fixed"><code>{% iterm "gem install ruby-progress" %}</code></pre></div></div>

<p>Renders:</p>

<div class="language-bash highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight fixed"><code>gem <span class="nb">install </span>ruby-progress</code></pre></div></div>

<div class="iterm-command"><a href="https://brettterpstra.comiterm2:/command?c=gem%20install%20ruby-progress" class="iterm-run-button">Run in iTerm</a></div>

<p>Key/value form (custom text, directory, language):</p>

<div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight fixed"><code>{% iterm command:"python -m http.server" directory:"~/Sites/project" text:"iTerm: Start dev server" language:"console" %}</code></pre></div></div>

<p>That outputs a fenced code block with the command and a small &ldquo;Run in iTerm&rdquo; link/button that uses iTerm2&rsquo;s URL scheme:</p>

<div class="language-console highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight fixed"><code><span class="go">python -m http.server
</span></code></pre></div></div>

<div class="iterm-command"><a href="https://brettterpstra.comiterm2:/command?c=python%20-m%20http.server&amp;d=%7E%2FSites%2Fproject" class="iterm-run-button">iTerm: Start dev server</a></div>

<p>Get the plugin and examples <a href="https://github.com/ttscoff/JekyllPlugins/tree/master/iTerm">on GitHub</a>.</p>

